hist(x= log(gapminder_dataset$pop))

plot(y = gapminder_dataset$lifeExp, x = log(gapminder_dataset$gdpPercap))

df1 <- gapminder_dataset %>% 
  select(country, lifeExp) %>% 
  filter(country == "South Africa" |
            country == "Ireland")
  
t.test(data = df1, lifeExp ~ country)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  lifeExp by country
## t = 10.067, df = 19.109, p-value = 4.466e-09
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  15.07022 22.97794
## sample estimates:
##      mean in group Ireland mean in group South Africa 
##                   73.01725                   53.99317

GGPLOT2

gapminder_dataset %>% 
  filter( gdpPercap < 50000) %>% 
  ggplot(aes( x= log(gdpPercap) , y = lifeExp , col = continent, size = pop)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.3) +
  geom_smooth(method = lm)

#faceted
gapminder_dataset %>% 
  filter( gdpPercap < 50000) %>% 
  ggplot(aes( x= log(gdpPercap) , y = lifeExp , col = year, size = pop)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.3) +
  geom_smooth(method = lm) +
  facet_wrap(~continent)

#Linear Regresion

summary(gapminder_dataset %>%
